# SEO, Performance & Web Best Practices

Every new page or component must factor in SEO and performance.

## Semantic HTML5
- Always use proper semantic structural tags: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`.
- Ensure there is precisely **one `<h1>`** per page, with a strictly logical heading hierarchy (`<h2>`, `<h3>`).
- Use descriptive, unique `id` attributes on interactive elements.

## Accessibility
- Optimize accessibility: proper ARIA labels, descriptive `alt` text for all media elements.
- Maintain high contrast ratios (WCAG AA minimum).
- Ensure keyboard navigability for all interactive elements.

## Performance (Core Web Vitals)
- Favor lazy loading (`React.lazy` / `Suspense`) for heavy 3D assets and large images.
- Optimize for LCP, CLS, and FID/INP metrics.
- Use `loading="lazy"` on images below the fold.
- Minimize bundle size — split code aggressively.

## Meta & SEO
- Every page must have a unique `<title>` and `<meta name="description">`.
- Use Open Graph and Twitter Card meta tags for social sharing.
- Ensure canonical URLs are set correctly.
